<TITLE> Hasina leaves Tuesday to attend SAARC summit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 26 (bdnews24.com)  Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina leaves for Bhutan on Tuesday morning to attend the 16th summit of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC). UPDATE The two-day summit will begin on Wednesday, with Bhutan, for the first time, hosting the eight-nation summit. Bhutan will chair the summit, with Afghanistan, India, Sri Lanka, Nepal, the Maldives and Pakistan comprising the other members of the forum. The region is home to more than 1.4 billion people. Hasina is expected to make a statement along with other leaders of the member countries at the inaugural session of the summit. On the sidelines of the summit, Hasina will hold bilateral meetings with South Asian leaders. She will be accompanied by the foreign minister Dipu Moni, the state minister for forest and environment Hassan Mahmud and a delegation of high officials. During the opening day the permanent secretariat of the SAARC Development Fund will be inaugurated. Hasina returns home on April 30. bdnews
